## Project Context

You are building the DTL-Global AI-powered client onboarding platform.
The single source of truth is DTL_MASTER_PLAN.md in the project root.
Read it BEFORE writing any code. Every decision must align with that plan.

## MANDATORY RULES — NEVER VIOLATE THESE

### Rule 001: Google Docstring Format
All Python functions and classes MUST use Google-style docstrings.
Include: description, Args, Returns, Raises (where applicable).

### Rule 002: Comment Every Line
Every meaningful line of code MUST have an inline comment explaining what it does.
Group related lines under a block comment if they perform one logical step.
Goal: Gerardo can read any file and understand it without external docs.

### Rule 003: No Over-Engineering
Do NOT add:
- AWS services not listed in DTL_MASTER_PLAN.md Section 3
- Extra abstractions, design patterns, or frameworks
- Monitoring/observability tools (basic CloudWatch Lambda logs are fine)
- Docker, ECS, EKS, Fargate, EC2, or any container/compute services
- Step Functions, EventBridge, SQS, SNS unless explicitly in the plan
- ANY always-on compute — this is 100% SERVERLESS

### Rule 004: Clean Up Obsolete Files
When a phase is complete or a file is replaced:
- Delete obsolete .md planning files created during development
- Delete scratch/temp files
- Keep only: source code, tests, config files, DTL_MASTER_PLAN.md, README.md, docs/AUTHENTICATION.md

### Rule 005: Python Only
- All backend code: Python 3.12+
- All CDK code: Python
- All Lambda functions: Python
- All scripts: Python
- No TypeScript, no JavaScript backend

### Rule 006: Do Not Deviate From the Plan
Before creating any new file or service:
1. Check DTL_MASTER_PLAN.md to confirm it is listed
2. If not listed, ASK Gerardo before proceeding
3. Never add nice to have features

### Rule 007: Phase Gate Enforcement
Do NOT start a new phase until the current phase gate checklist
(DTL_MASTER_PLAN.md Section 21) is fully satisfied.

### Rule 008: File Naming Conventions
- Python files: snake_case (e.g., hubspot_setup.py)
- CDK stacks: snake_case with _stack suffix (e.g., api_stack.py)
- Lambda handlers: handler_{function_name}.py
- Tests: test_{module_name}.py
- Templates: {industry}_template.json

### Rule 009: Error Handling
All API calls (HubSpot, Stripe, AWS, AI) MUST have:
- try/except blocks with specific exception types
- Meaningful error messages including the operation that failed
- Graceful degradation (do not crash the whole onboarding if one step fails)
- Print statements for debugging (no logging frameworks)

### Rule 010: Secrets Management
- All API keys/secrets in AWS SSM Parameter Store (SecureString) under `/dtl-global-platform/` paths (see DTL_MASTER_PLAN.md Appendix C)
- NEVER hardcode secrets in source code
- Lambda uses env vars that reference SSM parameters
- .env files for LOCAL dev only, MUST be in .gitignore

### Rule 011: 100% Serverless
No exceptions. No EC2, no containers, no always-on compute.
Everything runs on Lambda, triggered by API Gateway or events.
Data in DynamoDB and S3 only.

### Rule 012: GitFlow (MANDATORY for every phase)
Enforces feature branches, GitHub Issues, PRs, and non-interactive CLI only (see DTL_MASTER_PLAN.md Section 20).

**One-time setup:** ensure a GitHub Project exists, e.g. `gh project create --title "DTL-Global Platform" --owner @me` (create once, reuse).

**Before each phase (Phase 1 onward):** create a GitHub Issue describing the work; create a feature branch from `main` named `feature/{issue-number}-phase-{N}-{short-description}`.

**During the phase:** make granular commits; use message format `feat(phase-{N}): {description} #{issue-number}`; reference the issue in every commit.

**After the phase:** push the feature branch; open a PR with a written summary using `gh pr create ... --body "..."` (never `--editor`); merge with `gh pr merge --squash --delete-branch --yes`.

**Never:** commit directly to `main`; use interactive git/gh editors or prompts; omit `--body`, `--yes`, or `-m` where a non-interactive flow requires them.

**Always:** one feature branch and one PR per phase; squash-merge to keep `main` linear.

## Approved AWS Services (ONLY THESE)
Lambda, API Gateway (REST), DynamoDB, S3, CloudFront, Route 53, ACM, SES,
SSM Parameter Store, CodePipeline, CodeBuild, CloudWatch Logs (auto).

## Approved External APIs
HubSpot CRM API (Bearer token from developer platform 2025.2 static-auth app in `hubspot/dtl-global-platform-app/`; see docs/AUTHENTICATION.md),
Stripe API (Python SDK), Stripe Connect,
Anthropic Claude API (Direct — Haiku 4.5), Google Workspace Admin API (future).

## When Unsure
If the plan does not cover something, ASK Gerardo — do not assume or add features.